{
  "text": "In summary, Tollip regulates the magnitude and kinetics of IL-6 and TNF-\u2423 production upon stimulation with IL-1\u2424 and low doses or physiological doses of LPS. We did not observe any effect of Tollip deficiency in response to lethal doses of LPS, suggesting that Tollip acts in \"fine tuning\" or coordinating optimal signaling through IL-1RI and TLR4. In this way, Tollip resembles a scaffolding protein that is required for optimal responses. As such, high concentrations of Tollip may titrate out critical signaling proteins in IL-1R and TLR4 pathways, thereby blocking signaling. This would accommodate the apparently conflicting observations (i.e., repressor versus activator) and predicts that the cellular concentration of Tollip may be crucial for its capacity to regulate signaling. Further it could explain why overexpression or upregulation of Tollip in intestinal epithelial cells correlates with a hyporesponsive state, after a second challenge with a TLR ligand [CITATION_1] .",
